[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Gradle and JUnit Issues**\n\nI'm looking into the Gradle error output and exploring issues related to classes like GitUtil and ScmTagParameters. It seems that the use of `GitUtil.getSettings().setGitCommand` might cause global modifications across tests. JUnit might not manage parallel tests within a class, which could affect other tests running in the same JVM. Maybe it would be wise to avoid parallel execution for robustness. Also, I'm wondering about native image execution and the usability of `Files.writeString` in script execution. There's potential for capturing tag commands and file management in temporary directories as well.\n\n**Exploring File and Command Issues**\n\nI’m considering operating system paths and how a backslash might work on some platforms, but not on Linux. Regarding the usage of `FileUtils.createTempFile`, I think the suffix can indeed be `.commit` and possibly include randomness after that. It's good to ensure that all individual tests run within 60 seconds since shell executions are typically fast. I’m also looking into dynamic access coverage and its effectiveness, plus if there’s a deprecation warning from `GitCheckInCommand.createCommitCommandLine`, it might be worth using `javap -v` to check.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0aead4cd9bebb897016a2a61c04710819097d1a187426f29e2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKmHNFz5nBPlpTRinMhZboqv7-zrk7wCuwOcTdAeAGQ-eyLooiQjiaGJvLwdEBHMt3dxE6O8aeSMQaZrz6j-VPYOkozKGSTMDrwmWuUBCP2wEyns7ObavGi6eNzJus8IGoLfKRrCue79kwzS0GcAlRYLsqqqO6xSOup7Uk1as5WflYzVbzokEd_vyO20cS3_FUMY2W8GnyXsFSfkhZYoAUoMq5AAi0B4SIe5Fgbq5AaV--IpHvUdrJ15bYpMFkgJibeLQGVyrFs5p9sUsK0nVQZYlRcMboA7eX9B79aS_nedQ_Mb-ZPwM1EKy3TwoyjLOIx5A1G1ZMQuHblpU1opjQfwjYKNWWIzrrjZKTgjqcRdhrCHwrt1AQlGpj7_1PHHoda8-LyeLWZfHg-szuYKMR3Chyw9m1l_3Xo4OXN-wUb2aewQyaAg9GLu27RTsXYK3nfRm40WassWl_rpvrzPffJtsdmV